56// The number of RTCP time intervals needed to trigger a timeout.
57const int kRrTimeoutIntervals = 3;
58
59const int64_t kTmmbrTimeoutIntervalMs = 5 * 5000;
60
61const int64_t kMaxWarningLogIntervalMs = 10000;
62const int64_t kRtcpMinFrameLengthMs = 17;
63
64// Maximum number of received RRTRs that will be stored.
65const size_t kMaxNumberOfStoredRrtrs = 300;
66
67constexpr TimeDelta kDefaultVideoReportInterval = TimeDelta::Seconds(1);
68constexpr TimeDelta kDefaultAudioReportInterval = TimeDelta::Seconds(5);
69
70// Returns true if the |timestamp| has exceeded the |interval *
71// kRrTimeoutIntervals| period and was reset (set to PlusInfinity()). Returns
72// false if the timer was either already reset or if it has not expired.
73bool ResetTimestampIfExpired(const Timestamp now,
74 Timestamp& timestamp,
75 TimeDelta interval) {
76 if (timestamp.IsInfinite() ||
77 now <= timestamp + interval * kRrTimeoutIntervals) {
78 return false;
79 }
80
81 timestamp = Timestamp::PlusInfinity();
82 return true;
83}

87RTCPReceiver::RegisteredSsrcs::RegisteredSsrcs(
88 const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config) {
89 ssrcs_.push_back(config.local_media_ssrc);
90 if (config.rtx_send_ssrc) {
91 ssrcs_.push_back(*config.rtx_send_ssrc);
92 }
93 if (config.fec_generator) {
94 absl::optional<uint32_t> flexfec_ssrc = config.fec_generator->FecSsrc();
95 if (flexfec_ssrc) {
96 ssrcs_.push_back(*flexfec_ssrc);
97 }
98 }
99 // Ensure that the RegisteredSsrcs can inline the SSRCs.
100 RTC_DCHECK_LE(ssrcs_.size(), RTCPReceiver::RegisteredSsrcs::kMaxSsrcs);
101}

103struct RTCPReceiver::PacketInformation {
104 uint32_t packet_type_flags = 0; // RTCPPacketTypeFlags bit field.
105
106 uint32_t remote_ssrc = 0;
107 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_sequence_numbers;
108 // TODO(hbos): Remove |report_blocks| in favor of |report_block_datas|.
109 ReportBlockList report_blocks;
110 std::vector<ReportBlockData> report_block_datas;
111 int64_t rtt_ms = 0;
112 uint32_t receiver_estimated_max_bitrate_bps = 0;
113 std::unique_ptr<rtcp::TransportFeedback> transport_feedback;
114 absl::optional<VideoBitrateAllocation> target_bitrate_allocation;
115 absl::optional<NetworkStateEstimate> network_state_estimate;
116 std::unique_ptr<rtcp::LossNotification> loss_notification;
117};

119RTCPReceiver::RTCPReceiver(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config,
120 ModuleRtpRtcp* owner)
121 : clock_(config.clock),
122 receiver_only_(config.receiver_only),
123 rtp_rtcp_(owner),
124 main_ssrc_(config.local_media_ssrc),
125 registered_ssrcs_(config),
126 rtcp_bandwidth_observer_(config.bandwidth_callback),
127 rtcp_intra_frame_observer_(config.intra_frame_callback),
128 rtcp_loss_notification_observer_(config.rtcp_loss_notification_observer),
129 network_state_estimate_observer_(config.network_state_estimate_observer),
130 transport_feedback_observer_(config.transport_feedback_callback),
131 bitrate_allocation_observer_(config.bitrate_allocation_observer),
132 report_interval_(config.rtcp_report_interval_ms > 0
133 ? TimeDelta::Millis(config.rtcp_report_interval_ms)
134 : (config.audio ? kDefaultAudioReportInterval
135 : kDefaultVideoReportInterval)),
136 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10774): Remove fallback.
137 remote_ssrc_(0),
138 remote_sender_rtp_time_(0),
139 remote_sender_packet_count_(0),
140 remote_sender_octet_count_(0),
141 remote_sender_reports_count_(0),
142 xr_rrtr_status_(config.non_sender_rtt_measurement),
143 xr_rr_rtt_ms_(0),
144 oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_(0),
145 cname_callback_(config.rtcp_cname_callback),
146 report_block_data_observer_(config.report_block_data_observer),
147 packet_type_counter_observer_(config.rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer),
148 num_skipped_packets_(0),
149 last_skipped_packets_warning_ms_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()) {
150 RTC_DCHECK(owner);
151}

153RTCPReceiver::~RTCPReceiver() {}

155void RTCPReceiver::IncomingPacket(rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet) {
156 if (packet.empty()) {
157 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Incoming empty RTCP packet";
158 return;
159 }
160
161 PacketInformation packet_information;
162 if (!ParseCompoundPacket(packet, &packet_information))
163 return;
164 TriggerCallbacksFromRtcpPacket(packet_information);
165}

174void RTCPReceiver::SetRemoteSSRC(uint32_t ssrc) {
175 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
176 // New SSRC reset old reports.
177 last_received_sr_ntp_.Reset();
178 remote_ssrc_ = ssrc;
179}

181uint32_t RTCPReceiver::RemoteSSRC() const {
182 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
183 return remote_ssrc_;

186int32_t RTCPReceiver::RTT(uint32_t remote_ssrc,
187 int64_t* last_rtt_ms,
188 int64_t* avg_rtt_ms,
189 int64_t* min_rtt_ms,
190 int64_t* max_rtt_ms) const {
191 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
192
193 auto it = received_report_blocks_.find(main_ssrc_);
194 if (it == received_report_blocks_.end())
195 return -1;
196
197 auto it_info = it->second.find(remote_ssrc);
198 if (it_info == it->second.end())
199 return -1;
200
201 const ReportBlockData* report_block_data = &it_info->second;
202
203 if (report_block_data->num_rtts() == 0)
204 return -1;
205
206 if (last_rtt_ms)
207 *last_rtt_ms = report_block_data->last_rtt_ms();
208
209 if (avg_rtt_ms) {
210 *avg_rtt_ms =
211 report_block_data->sum_rtt_ms() / report_block_data->num_rtts();
212 }
213
214 if (min_rtt_ms)
215 *min_rtt_ms = report_block_data->min_rtt_ms();
216
217 if (max_rtt_ms)
218 *max_rtt_ms = report_block_data->max_rtt_ms();
219
220 return 0;
221}
222
223bool RTCPReceiver::GetAndResetXrRrRtt(int64_t* rtt_ms) {
224 RTC_DCHECK(rtt_ms);
225 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
226 if (xr_rr_rtt_ms_ == 0) {
227 return false;
228 }
229 *rtt_ms = xr_rr_rtt_ms_;
230 xr_rr_rtt_ms_ = 0;
231 return true;
232}
233
234// Called regularly (1/sec) on the worker thread to do rtt calculations.
235absl::optional<TimeDelta> RTCPReceiver::OnPeriodicRttUpdate(
236 Timestamp newer_than,
237 bool sending) {
238 // Running on the worker thread (same as construction thread).
239 absl::optional<TimeDelta> rtt;
240
241 if (sending) {
242 // Check if we've received a report block within the last kRttUpdateInterval
243 // amount of time.
244 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
245 if (last_received_rb_.IsInfinite() || last_received_rb_ > newer_than) {
246 // Stow away the report block for the main ssrc. We'll use the associated
247 // data map to look up each sender and check the last_rtt_ms().
248 auto main_report_it = received_report_blocks_.find(main_ssrc_);
249 if (main_report_it != received_report_blocks_.end()) {
250 const ReportBlockDataMap& main_data_map = main_report_it->second;
251 int64_t max_rtt = 0;
252 for (const auto& reports_per_receiver : received_report_blocks_) {
253 for (const auto& report : reports_per_receiver.second) {
254 const RTCPReportBlock& block = report.second.report_block();
255 auto it_info = main_data_map.find(block.sender_ssrc);
256 if (it_info != main_data_map.end()) {
257 const ReportBlockData* report_block_data = &it_info->second;
258 if (report_block_data->num_rtts() > 0) {
259 max_rtt = std::max(report_block_data->last_rtt_ms(), max_rtt);
260 }
261 }
262 }
263 }
264 if (max_rtt)
265 rtt.emplace(TimeDelta::Millis(max_rtt));
266 }
267 }
268
269 // Check for expired timers and if so, log and reset.
270 auto now = clock_->CurrentTime();
271 if (RtcpRrTimeoutLocked(now)) {
272 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "Timeout: No RTCP RR received.";
273 } else if (RtcpRrSequenceNumberTimeoutLocked(now)) {
274 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "Timeout: No increase in RTCP RR extended "
275 "highest sequence number.";
276 }
277 } else {
278 // Report rtt from receiver.
279 int64_t rtt_ms;
280 if (GetAndResetXrRrRtt(&rtt_ms)) {
281 rtt.emplace(TimeDelta::Millis(rtt_ms));
282 }
283 }
284
285 return rtt;
286}

288bool RTCPReceiver::NTP(uint32_t* received_ntp_secs,
289 uint32_t* received_ntp_frac,
290 uint32_t* rtcp_arrival_time_secs,
291 uint32_t* rtcp_arrival_time_frac,
292 uint32_t* rtcp_timestamp,
293 uint32_t* remote_sender_packet_count,
294 uint64_t* remote_sender_octet_count,
295 uint64_t* remote_sender_reports_count) const {
296 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
297 if (!last_received_sr_ntp_.Valid())
298 return false;
299
300 // NTP from incoming SenderReport.
301 if (received_ntp_secs)
302 *received_ntp_secs = remote_sender_ntp_time_.seconds();
303 if (received_ntp_frac)
304 *received_ntp_frac = remote_sender_ntp_time_.fractions();
305 // Rtp time from incoming SenderReport.
306 if (rtcp_timestamp)
307 *rtcp_timestamp = remote_sender_rtp_time_;
308
309 // Local NTP time when we received a RTCP packet with a send block.
310 if (rtcp_arrival_time_secs)
311 *rtcp_arrival_time_secs = last_received_sr_ntp_.seconds();
312 if (rtcp_arrival_time_frac)
313 *rtcp_arrival_time_frac = last_received_sr_ntp_.fractions();
314
315 // Counters.
316 if (remote_sender_packet_count)
317 *remote_sender_packet_count = remote_sender_packet_count_;
318 if (remote_sender_octet_count)
319 *remote_sender_octet_count = remote_sender_octet_count_;
320 if (remote_sender_reports_count)
321 *remote_sender_reports_count = remote_sender_reports_count_;
322
323 return true;
324}

326std::vector<rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo>
327RTCPReceiver::ConsumeReceivedXrReferenceTimeInfo() {
328 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
329
330 const size_t last_xr_rtis_size = std::min(
331 received_rrtrs_.size(), rtcp::ExtendedReports::kMaxNumberOfDlrrItems);
332 std::vector<rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo> last_xr_rtis;
333 last_xr_rtis.reserve(last_xr_rtis_size);
334
335 const uint32_t now_ntp =
336 CompactNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds()));
337
338 for (size_t i = 0; i < last_xr_rtis_size; ++i) {
339 RrtrInformation& rrtr = received_rrtrs_.front();
340 last_xr_rtis.emplace_back(rrtr.ssrc, rrtr.received_remote_mid_ntp_time,
341 now_ntp - rrtr.local_receive_mid_ntp_time);
342 received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_.erase(rrtr.ssrc);
343 received_rrtrs_.pop_front();
344 }
345
346 return last_xr_rtis;
347}
348
349std::vector<ReportBlockData> RTCPReceiver::GetLatestReportBlockData() const {
350 std::vector<ReportBlockData> result;
351 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
352 for (const auto& reports_per_receiver : received_report_blocks_)
353 for (const auto& report : reports_per_receiver.second)
354 result.push_back(report.second);
355 return result;
356}
357
358bool RTCPReceiver::ParseCompoundPacket(rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet,
359 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
360 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
361
362 CommonHeader rtcp_block;
363 for (const uint8_t* next_block = packet.begin(); next_block != packet.end();
364 next_block = rtcp_block.NextPacket()) {
365 ptrdiff_t remaining_blocks_size = packet.end() - next_block;
366 RTC_DCHECK_GT(remaining_blocks_size, 0);
367 if (!rtcp_block.Parse(next_block, remaining_blocks_size)) {
368 if (next_block == packet.begin()) {
369 // Failed to parse 1st header, nothing was extracted from this packet.
370 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Incoming invalid RTCP packet";
371 return false;
372 }
373 ++num_skipped_packets_;
374 break;
375 }
376
377 if (packet_type_counter_.first_packet_time_ms == -1)
378 packet_type_counter_.first_packet_time_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
379
380 switch (rtcp_block.type()) {
381 case rtcp::SenderReport::kPacketType:
382 HandleSenderReport(rtcp_block, packet_information);
383 break;
384 case rtcp::ReceiverReport::kPacketType:
385 HandleReceiverReport(rtcp_block, packet_information);
386 break;
387 case rtcp::Sdes::kPacketType:
388 HandleSdes(rtcp_block, packet_information);
389 break;
390 case rtcp::ExtendedReports::kPacketType:
391 HandleXr(rtcp_block, packet_information);
392 break;
393 case rtcp::Bye::kPacketType:
394 HandleBye(rtcp_block);
395 break;
396 case rtcp::App::kPacketType:
397 HandleApp(rtcp_block, packet_information);
398 break;
399 case rtcp::Rtpfb::kPacketType:
400 switch (rtcp_block.fmt()) {
401 case rtcp::Nack::kFeedbackMessageType:
402 HandleNack(rtcp_block, packet_information);
403 break;
404 case rtcp::Tmmbr::kFeedbackMessageType:
405 HandleTmmbr(rtcp_block, packet_information);
406 break;
407 case rtcp::Tmmbn::kFeedbackMessageType:
408 HandleTmmbn(rtcp_block, packet_information);
409 break;
410 case rtcp::RapidResyncRequest::kFeedbackMessageType:
411 HandleSrReq(rtcp_block, packet_information);
412 break;
413 case rtcp::TransportFeedback::kFeedbackMessageType:
414 HandleTransportFeedback(rtcp_block, packet_information);
415 break;
416 default:
417 ++num_skipped_packets_;
418 break;
419 }
420 break;
421 case rtcp::Psfb::kPacketType:
422 switch (rtcp_block.fmt()) {
423 case rtcp::Pli::kFeedbackMessageType:
424 HandlePli(rtcp_block, packet_information);
425 break;
426 case rtcp::Fir::kFeedbackMessageType:
427 HandleFir(rtcp_block, packet_information);
428 break;
429 case rtcp::Psfb::kAfbMessageType:
430 HandlePsfbApp(rtcp_block, packet_information);
431 break;
432 default:
433 ++num_skipped_packets_;
434 break;
435 }
436 break;
437 default:
438 ++num_skipped_packets_;
439 break;
440 }
441 }
442
443 if (packet_type_counter_observer_) {
444 packet_type_counter_observer_->RtcpPacketTypesCounterUpdated(
445 main_ssrc_, packet_type_counter_);
446 }
447
448 if (num_skipped_packets_ > 0) {
449 const int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
450 if (now_ms - last_skipped_packets_warning_ms_ >= kMaxWarningLogIntervalMs) {
451 last_skipped_packets_warning_ms_ = now_ms;
452 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
453 << num_skipped_packets_
454 << " RTCP blocks were skipped due to being malformed or of "
455 "unrecognized/unsupported type, during the past "
456 << (kMaxWarningLogIntervalMs / 1000) << " second period.";
457 }
458 }
459
460 return true;
461}
462
463void RTCPReceiver::HandleSenderReport(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
464 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
465 rtcp::SenderReport sender_report;
466 if (!sender_report.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
467 ++num_skipped_packets_;
468 return;
469 }
470
471 const uint32_t remote_ssrc = sender_report.sender_ssrc();
472
473 packet_information->remote_ssrc = remote_ssrc;
474
475 UpdateTmmbrRemoteIsAlive(remote_ssrc);
476
477 // Have I received RTP packets from this party?
478 if (remote_ssrc_ == remote_ssrc) {
479 // Only signal that we have received a SR when we accept one.
480 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpSr;
481
482 remote_sender_ntp_time_ = sender_report.ntp();
483 remote_sender_rtp_time_ = sender_report.rtp_timestamp();
484 last_received_sr_ntp_ = TimeMicrosToNtp(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds());
485 remote_sender_packet_count_ = sender_report.sender_packet_count();
486 remote_sender_octet_count_ = sender_report.sender_octet_count();
487 remote_sender_reports_count_++;
488 } else {
489 // We will only store the send report from one source, but
490 // we will store all the receive blocks.
491 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpRr;
492 }
493
494 for (const rtcp::ReportBlock& report_block : sender_report.report_blocks())
495 HandleReportBlock(report_block, packet_information, remote_ssrc);
496}
497
498void RTCPReceiver::HandleReceiverReport(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
499 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
500 rtcp::ReceiverReport receiver_report;
501 if (!receiver_report.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
502 ++num_skipped_packets_;
503 return;
504 }
505
506 const uint32_t remote_ssrc = receiver_report.sender_ssrc();
507
508 packet_information->remote_ssrc = remote_ssrc;
509
510 UpdateTmmbrRemoteIsAlive(remote_ssrc);
511
512 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpRr;
513
514 for (const ReportBlock& report_block : receiver_report.report_blocks())
515 HandleReportBlock(report_block, packet_information, remote_ssrc);
516}
517
518void RTCPReceiver::HandleReportBlock(const ReportBlock& report_block,
519 PacketInformation* packet_information,
520 uint32_t remote_ssrc) {
521 // This will be called once per report block in the RTCP packet.
522 // We filter out all report blocks that are not for us.
523 // Each packet has max 31 RR blocks.
524 //
525 // We can calc RTT if we send a send report and get a report block back.
526
527 // |report_block.source_ssrc()| is the SSRC identifier of the source to
528 // which the information in this reception report block pertains.
529
530 // Filter out all report blocks that are not for us.
531 if (!registered_ssrcs_.contains(report_block.source_ssrc()))
532 return;
533
534 last_received_rb_ = clock_->CurrentTime();
535
536 ReportBlockData* report_block_data =
537 &received_report_blocks_[report_block.source_ssrc()][remote_ssrc];
538 RTCPReportBlock rtcp_report_block;
539 rtcp_report_block.sender_ssrc = remote_ssrc;
540 rtcp_report_block.source_ssrc = report_block.source_ssrc();
541 rtcp_report_block.fraction_lost = report_block.fraction_lost();
542 rtcp_report_block.packets_lost = report_block.cumulative_lost_signed();
543 if (report_block.extended_high_seq_num() >
544 report_block_data->report_block().extended_highest_sequence_number) {
545 // We have successfully delivered new RTP packets to the remote side after
546 // the last RR was sent from the remote side.
547 last_increased_sequence_number_ = last_received_rb_;
548 }
549 rtcp_report_block.extended_highest_sequence_number =
550 report_block.extended_high_seq_num();
551 rtcp_report_block.jitter = report_block.jitter();
552 rtcp_report_block.delay_since_last_sender_report =
553 report_block.delay_since_last_sr();
554 rtcp_report_block.last_sender_report_timestamp = report_block.last_sr();
555 report_block_data->SetReportBlock(rtcp_report_block, rtc::TimeUTCMicros());
556
557 int64_t rtt_ms = 0;
558 uint32_t send_time_ntp = report_block.last_sr();
559 // RFC3550, section 6.4.1, LSR field discription states:
560 // If no SR has been received yet, the field is set to zero.
561 // Receiver rtp_rtcp module is not expected to calculate rtt using
562 // Sender Reports even if it accidentally can.
563
564 // TODO(nisse): Use this way to determine the RTT only when |receiver_only_|
565 // is false. However, that currently breaks the tests of the
566 // googCaptureStartNtpTimeMs stat for audio receive streams. To fix, either
567 // delete all dependencies on RTT measurements for audio receive streams, or
568 // ensure that audio receive streams that need RTT and stats that depend on it
569 // are configured with an associated audio send stream.
570 if (send_time_ntp != 0) {
571 uint32_t delay_ntp = report_block.delay_since_last_sr();
572 // Local NTP time.
573 uint32_t receive_time_ntp =
574 CompactNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(last_received_rb_.us()));
575
576 // RTT in 1/(2^16) seconds.
577 uint32_t rtt_ntp = receive_time_ntp - delay_ntp - send_time_ntp;
578 // Convert to 1/1000 seconds (milliseconds).
579 rtt_ms = CompactNtpRttToMs(rtt_ntp);
580 report_block_data->AddRoundTripTimeSample(rtt_ms);
581
582 packet_information->rtt_ms = rtt_ms;
583 }
584
585 packet_information->report_blocks.push_back(
586 report_block_data->report_block());
587 packet_information->report_block_datas.push_back(*report_block_data);
588}
589
590RTCPReceiver::TmmbrInformation* RTCPReceiver::FindOrCreateTmmbrInfo(
591 uint32_t remote_ssrc) {
592 // Create or find receive information.
593 TmmbrInformation* tmmbr_info = &tmmbr_infos_[remote_ssrc];
594 // Update that this remote is alive.
595 tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
596 return tmmbr_info;
597}
598
599void RTCPReceiver::UpdateTmmbrRemoteIsAlive(uint32_t remote_ssrc) {
600 auto tmmbr_it = tmmbr_infos_.find(remote_ssrc);
601 if (tmmbr_it != tmmbr_infos_.end())
602 tmmbr_it->second.last_time_received_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
603}
604
605RTCPReceiver::TmmbrInformation* RTCPReceiver::GetTmmbrInformation(
606 uint32_t remote_ssrc) {
607 auto it = tmmbr_infos_.find(remote_ssrc);
608 if (it == tmmbr_infos_.end())
609 return nullptr;
610 return &it->second;
611}
612
613// These two methods (RtcpRrTimeout and RtcpRrSequenceNumberTimeout) only exist
614// for tests and legacy code (rtp_rtcp_impl.cc). We should be able to to delete
615// the methods and require that access to the locked variables only happens on
616// the worker thread and thus no locking is needed.
617bool RTCPReceiver::RtcpRrTimeout() {
618 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
619 return RtcpRrTimeoutLocked(clock_->CurrentTime());
620}

622bool RTCPReceiver::RtcpRrSequenceNumberTimeout() {
623 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
624 return RtcpRrSequenceNumberTimeoutLocked(clock_->CurrentTime());
625}
626
627bool RTCPReceiver::UpdateTmmbrTimers() {
628 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
629
630 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
631 int64_t timeout_ms = now_ms - kTmmbrTimeoutIntervalMs;
632
633 if (oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_ >= timeout_ms)
634 return false;
635
636 bool update_bounding_set = false;
637 oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_ = -1;
638 for (auto tmmbr_it = tmmbr_infos_.begin(); tmmbr_it != tmmbr_infos_.end();) {
639 TmmbrInformation* tmmbr_info = &tmmbr_it->second;
640 if (tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms > 0) {
641 if (tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms < timeout_ms) {
642 // No rtcp packet for the last 5 regular intervals, reset limitations.
643 tmmbr_info->tmmbr.clear();
644 // Prevent that we call this over and over again.
645 tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms = 0;
646 // Send new TMMBN to all channels using the default codec.
647 update_bounding_set = true;
648 } else if (oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_ == -1 ||
649 tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms < oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_) {
650 oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_ = tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms;
651 }
652 ++tmmbr_it;
653 } else if (tmmbr_info->ready_for_delete) {
654 // When we dont have a last_time_received_ms and the object is marked
655 // ready_for_delete it's removed from the map.
656 tmmbr_it = tmmbr_infos_.erase(tmmbr_it);
657 } else {
658 ++tmmbr_it;
659 }
660 }
661 return update_bounding_set;
662}
663
664std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> RTCPReceiver::BoundingSet(bool* tmmbr_owner) {
665 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
666 TmmbrInformation* tmmbr_info = GetTmmbrInformation(remote_ssrc_);
667 if (!tmmbr_info)
668 return std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem>();
669
670 *tmmbr_owner = TMMBRHelp::IsOwner(tmmbr_info->tmmbn, main_ssrc_);
671 return tmmbr_info->tmmbn;
672}

674void RTCPReceiver::HandleSdes(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
675 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
676 rtcp::Sdes sdes;
677 if (!sdes.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
678 ++num_skipped_packets_;
679 return;
680 }
681
682 for (const rtcp::Sdes::Chunk& chunk : sdes.chunks()) {
683 if (cname_callback_)
684 cname_callback_->OnCname(chunk.ssrc, chunk.cname);
685 }
686 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpSdes;
687}
688
689void RTCPReceiver::HandleNack(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
690 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
691 rtcp::Nack nack;
692 if (!nack.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
693 ++num_skipped_packets_;
694 return;
695 }
696
697 if (receiver_only_ || main_ssrc_ != nack.media_ssrc()) // Not to us.
698 return;
699
700 packet_information->nack_sequence_numbers.insert(
701 packet_information->nack_sequence_numbers.end(),
702 nack.packet_ids().begin(), nack.packet_ids().end());
703 for (uint16_t packet_id : nack.packet_ids())
704 nack_stats_.ReportRequest(packet_id);
705
706 if (!nack.packet_ids().empty()) {
707 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpNack;
708 ++packet_type_counter_.nack_packets;
709 packet_type_counter_.nack_requests = nack_stats_.requests();
710 packet_type_counter_.unique_nack_requests = nack_stats_.unique_requests();
711 }
712}

714void RTCPReceiver::HandleApp(const rtcp::CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
715 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
716 rtcp::App app;
717 if (app.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
718 if (app.name() == rtcp::RemoteEstimate::kName &&
719 app.sub_type() == rtcp::RemoteEstimate::kSubType) {
720 rtcp::RemoteEstimate estimate(std::move(app));
721 if (estimate.ParseData()) {
722 packet_information->network_state_estimate = estimate.estimate();
723 return;
724 }
725 }
726 }
727 ++num_skipped_packets_;
728}
729
730void RTCPReceiver::HandleBye(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block) {
731 rtcp::Bye bye;
732 if (!bye.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
733 ++num_skipped_packets_;
734 return;
735 }
736
737 // Clear our lists.
738 for (auto& reports_per_receiver : received_report_blocks_)
739 reports_per_receiver.second.erase(bye.sender_ssrc());
740
741 TmmbrInformation* tmmbr_info = GetTmmbrInformation(bye.sender_ssrc());
742 if (tmmbr_info)
743 tmmbr_info->ready_for_delete = true;
744
745 last_fir_.erase(bye.sender_ssrc());
746 auto it = received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_.find(bye.sender_ssrc());
747 if (it != received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_.end()) {
748 received_rrtrs_.erase(it->second);
749 received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_.erase(it);
750 }
751 xr_rr_rtt_ms_ = 0;
752}
753
754void RTCPReceiver::HandleXr(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
755 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
756 rtcp::ExtendedReports xr;
757 if (!xr.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
758 ++num_skipped_packets_;
759 return;
760 }
761
762 if (xr.rrtr())
763 HandleXrReceiveReferenceTime(xr.sender_ssrc(), *xr.rrtr());
764
765 for (const rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo& time_info : xr.dlrr().sub_blocks())
766 HandleXrDlrrReportBlock(time_info);
767
768 if (xr.target_bitrate()) {
769 HandleXrTargetBitrate(xr.sender_ssrc(), *xr.target_bitrate(),
770 packet_information);
771 }
772}
773
774void RTCPReceiver::HandleXrReceiveReferenceTime(uint32_t sender_ssrc,
775 const rtcp::Rrtr& rrtr) {
776 uint32_t received_remote_mid_ntp_time = CompactNtp(rrtr.ntp());
777 uint32_t local_receive_mid_ntp_time =
778 CompactNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds()));
779
780 auto it = received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_.find(sender_ssrc);
781 if (it != received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_.end()) {
782 it->second->received_remote_mid_ntp_time = received_remote_mid_ntp_time;
783 it->second->local_receive_mid_ntp_time = local_receive_mid_ntp_time;
784 } else {
785 if (received_rrtrs_.size() < kMaxNumberOfStoredRrtrs) {
786 received_rrtrs_.emplace_back(sender_ssrc, received_remote_mid_ntp_time,
787 local_receive_mid_ntp_time);
788 received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_[sender_ssrc] = std::prev(received_rrtrs_.end());
789 } else {
790 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Discarding received RRTR for ssrc " << sender_ssrc
791 << ", reached maximum number of stored RRTRs.";
792 }
793 }
794}
795
796void RTCPReceiver::HandleXrDlrrReportBlock(const rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo& rti) {
797 if (!registered_ssrcs_.contains(rti.ssrc)) // Not to us.
798 return;
799
800 // Caller should explicitly enable rtt calculation using extended reports.
801 if (!xr_rrtr_status_)
802 return;
803
804 // The send_time and delay_rr fields are in units of 1/2^16 sec.
805 uint32_t send_time_ntp = rti.last_rr;
806 // RFC3611, section 4.5, LRR field discription states:
807 // If no such block has been received, the field is set to zero.
808 if (send_time_ntp == 0)
809 return;
810
811 uint32_t delay_ntp = rti.delay_since_last_rr;
812 uint32_t now_ntp = CompactNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds()));
813
814 uint32_t rtt_ntp = now_ntp - delay_ntp - send_time_ntp;
815 xr_rr_rtt_ms_ = CompactNtpRttToMs(rtt_ntp);
816}
817
818void RTCPReceiver::HandleXrTargetBitrate(
819 uint32_t ssrc,
820 const rtcp::TargetBitrate& target_bitrate,
821 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
822 if (ssrc != remote_ssrc_) {
823 return; // Not for us.
824 }
825
826 VideoBitrateAllocation bitrate_allocation;
827 for (const auto& item : target_bitrate.GetTargetBitrates()) {
828 if (item.spatial_layer >= kMaxSpatialLayers ||
829 item.temporal_layer >= kMaxTemporalStreams) {
830 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
831 << "Invalid layer in XR target bitrate pack: spatial index "
832 << item.spatial_layer << ", temporal index " << item.temporal_layer
833 << ", dropping.";
834 } else {
835 bitrate_allocation.SetBitrate(item.spatial_layer, item.temporal_layer,
836 item.target_bitrate_kbps * 1000);
837 }
838 }
839 packet_information->target_bitrate_allocation.emplace(bitrate_allocation);
840}

842void RTCPReceiver::HandlePli(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
843 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
844 rtcp::Pli pli;
845 if (!pli.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
846 ++num_skipped_packets_;
847 return;
848 }
849
850 if (main_ssrc_ == pli.media_ssrc()) {
851 ++packet_type_counter_.pli_packets;
852 // Received a signal that we need to send a new key frame.
853 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpPli;
854 }
855}
856
857void RTCPReceiver::HandleTmmbr(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
858 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
859 rtcp::Tmmbr tmmbr;
860 if (!tmmbr.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
861 ++num_skipped_packets_;
862 return;
863 }
864
865 uint32_t sender_ssrc = tmmbr.sender_ssrc();
866 if (tmmbr.media_ssrc()) {
867 // media_ssrc() SHOULD be 0 if same as SenderSSRC.
868 // In relay mode this is a valid number.
869 sender_ssrc = tmmbr.media_ssrc();
870 }
871
872 for (const rtcp::TmmbItem& request : tmmbr.requests()) {
873 if (main_ssrc_ != request.ssrc() || request.bitrate_bps() == 0)
874 continue;
875
876 TmmbrInformation* tmmbr_info = FindOrCreateTmmbrInfo(tmmbr.sender_ssrc());
877 auto* entry = &tmmbr_info->tmmbr[sender_ssrc];
878 entry->tmmbr_item = rtcp::TmmbItem(sender_ssrc, request.bitrate_bps(),
879 request.packet_overhead());
880 // FindOrCreateTmmbrInfo always sets |last_time_received_ms| to
881 // |clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()|.
882 entry->last_updated_ms = tmmbr_info->last_time_received_ms;
883
884 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpTmmbr;
885 break;
886 }
887}

892 if (!tmmbn.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
893 ++num_skipped_packets_;
894 return;

897 TmmbrInformation* tmmbr_info = FindOrCreateTmmbrInfo(tmmbn.sender_ssrc());
898
899 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpTmmbn;
900
901 tmmbr_info->tmmbn = tmmbn.items();
902}

915void RTCPReceiver::HandlePsfbApp(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
916 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
917 {
918 rtcp::Remb remb;
919 if (remb.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
920 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpRemb;
921 packet_information->receiver_estimated_max_bitrate_bps =
922 remb.bitrate_bps();
923 return;
924 }
925 }
926
927 {
928 auto loss_notification = std::make_unique<rtcp::LossNotification>();
929 if (loss_notification->Parse(rtcp_block)) {
930 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpLossNotification;
931 packet_information->loss_notification = std::move(loss_notification);
932 return;
933 }
934 }
935
936 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unknown PSFB-APP packet.";
937
938 ++num_skipped_packets_;
939}
940
941void RTCPReceiver::HandleFir(const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
942 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
943 rtcp::Fir fir;
944 if (!fir.Parse(rtcp_block)) {
945 ++num_skipped_packets_;
946 return;
947 }
948
949 if (fir.requests().empty())
950 return;
951
952 const int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
953 for (const rtcp::Fir::Request& fir_request : fir.requests()) {
954 // Is it our sender that is requested to generate a new keyframe.
955 if (main_ssrc_ != fir_request.ssrc)
956 continue;
957
958 ++packet_type_counter_.fir_packets;
959
960 auto inserted = last_fir_.insert(std::make_pair(
961 fir.sender_ssrc(), LastFirStatus(now_ms, fir_request.seq_nr)));
962 if (!inserted.second) { // There was already an entry.
963 LastFirStatus* last_fir = &inserted.first->second;
964
965 // Check if we have reported this FIRSequenceNumber before.
966 if (fir_request.seq_nr == last_fir->sequence_number)
967 continue;
968
969 // Sanity: don't go crazy with the callbacks.
970 if (now_ms - last_fir->request_ms < kRtcpMinFrameLengthMs)
971 continue;
972
973 last_fir->request_ms = now_ms;
974 last_fir->sequence_number = fir_request.seq_nr;
975 }
976 // Received signal that we need to send a new key frame.
977 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpFir;
978 }
979}

981void RTCPReceiver::HandleTransportFeedback(
982 const CommonHeader& rtcp_block,
983 PacketInformation* packet_information) {
984 std::unique_ptr<rtcp::TransportFeedback> transport_feedback(
985 new rtcp::TransportFeedback());
986 if (!transport_feedback->Parse(rtcp_block)) {
987 ++num_skipped_packets_;
988 return;
989 }
990
991 packet_information->packet_type_flags |= kRtcpTransportFeedback;
992 packet_information->transport_feedback = std::move(transport_feedback);
993}
994
995void RTCPReceiver::NotifyTmmbrUpdated() {
996 // Find bounding set.
997 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> bounding =
998 TMMBRHelp::FindBoundingSet(TmmbrReceived());
999
1000 if (!bounding.empty() && rtcp_bandwidth_observer_) {
1001 // We have a new bandwidth estimate on this channel.
1002 uint64_t bitrate_bps = TMMBRHelp::CalcMinBitrateBps(bounding);
1003 if (bitrate_bps <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max())
1004 rtcp_bandwidth_observer_->OnReceivedEstimatedBitrate(bitrate_bps);
1005 }
1006
1007 // Send tmmbn to inform remote clients about the new bandwidth.
1008 rtp_rtcp_->SetTmmbn(std::move(bounding));
1009}
1010
1011// Holding no Critical section.
1012void RTCPReceiver::TriggerCallbacksFromRtcpPacket(
1013 const PacketInformation& packet_information) {
1014 // Process TMMBR and REMB first to avoid multiple callbacks
1015 // to OnNetworkChanged.
1016 if (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpTmmbr) {
1017 // Might trigger a OnReceivedBandwidthEstimateUpdate.
1018 NotifyTmmbrUpdated();
1019 }
1020
1021 if (!receiver_only_ && (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpSrReq)) {
1022 rtp_rtcp_->OnRequestSendReport();
1023 }
1024 if (!receiver_only_ && (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpNack)) {
1025 if (!packet_information.nack_sequence_numbers.empty()) {
1026 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Incoming NACK length: "
1027 << packet_information.nack_sequence_numbers.size();
1028 rtp_rtcp_->OnReceivedNack(packet_information.nack_sequence_numbers);
1029 }
1030 }
1031
1032 // We need feedback that we have received a report block(s) so that we
1033 // can generate a new packet in a conference relay scenario, one received
1034 // report can generate several RTCP packets, based on number relayed/mixed
1035 // a send report block should go out to all receivers.
1036 if (rtcp_intra_frame_observer_) {
1037 RTC_DCHECK(!receiver_only_);
1038 if ((packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpPli) ||
1039 (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpFir)) {
1040 if (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpPli) {
1041 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
1042 << "Incoming PLI from SSRC " << packet_information.remote_ssrc;
1043 } else {
1044 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
1045 << "Incoming FIR from SSRC " << packet_information.remote_ssrc;
1046 }
1047 rtcp_intra_frame_observer_->OnReceivedIntraFrameRequest(main_ssrc_);
1048 }
1049 }
1050 if (rtcp_loss_notification_observer_ &&
1051 (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpLossNotification)) {
1052 rtcp::LossNotification* loss_notification =
1053 packet_information.loss_notification.get();
1054 RTC_DCHECK(loss_notification);
1055 if (loss_notification->media_ssrc() == main_ssrc_) {
1056 rtcp_loss_notification_observer_->OnReceivedLossNotification(
1057 loss_notification->media_ssrc(), loss_notification->last_decoded(),
1058 loss_notification->last_received(),
1059 loss_notification->decodability_flag());
1060 }
1061 }
1062 if (rtcp_bandwidth_observer_) {
1063 RTC_DCHECK(!receiver_only_);
1064 if (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpRemb) {
1065 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
1066 << "Incoming REMB: "
1067 << packet_information.receiver_estimated_max_bitrate_bps;
1068 rtcp_bandwidth_observer_->OnReceivedEstimatedBitrate(
1069 packet_information.receiver_estimated_max_bitrate_bps);
1070 }
1071 if ((packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpSr) ||
1072 (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpRr)) {
1073 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
1074 rtcp_bandwidth_observer_->OnReceivedRtcpReceiverReport(
1075 packet_information.report_blocks, packet_information.rtt_ms, now_ms);
1076 }
1077 }
1078 if ((packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpSr) ||
1079 (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpRr)) {
1080 rtp_rtcp_->OnReceivedRtcpReportBlocks(packet_information.report_blocks);
1081 }
1082
1083 if (transport_feedback_observer_ &&
1084 (packet_information.packet_type_flags & kRtcpTransportFeedback)) {
1085 uint32_t media_source_ssrc =
1086 packet_information.transport_feedback->media_ssrc();
1087 if (media_source_ssrc == main_ssrc_ ||
1088 registered_ssrcs_.contains(media_source_ssrc)) {
1089 transport_feedback_observer_->OnTransportFeedback(
1090 *packet_information.transport_feedback);
1091 }
1092 }
1093
1094 if (network_state_estimate_observer_ &&
1095 packet_information.network_state_estimate) {
1096 network_state_estimate_observer_->OnRemoteNetworkEstimate(
1097 *packet_information.network_state_estimate);
1098 }
1099
1100 if (bitrate_allocation_observer_ &&
1101 packet_information.target_bitrate_allocation) {
1102 bitrate_allocation_observer_->OnBitrateAllocationUpdated(
1103 *packet_information.target_bitrate_allocation);
1104 }
1105
1106 if (!receiver_only_) {
1107 if (report_block_data_observer_) {
1108 for (const auto& report_block_data :
1109 packet_information.report_block_datas) {
1110 report_block_data_observer_->OnReportBlockDataUpdated(
1111 report_block_data);
1112 }
1113 }
1114 }
1115}
1116
1117std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> RTCPReceiver::TmmbrReceived() {
1118 MutexLock lock(&rtcp_receiver_lock_);
1119 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> candidates;
1120
1121 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
1122 int64_t timeout_ms = now_ms - kTmmbrTimeoutIntervalMs;
1123
1124 for (auto& kv : tmmbr_infos_) {
1125 for (auto it = kv.second.tmmbr.begin(); it != kv.second.tmmbr.end();) {
1126 if (it->second.last_updated_ms < timeout_ms) {
1127 // Erase timeout entries.
1128 it = kv.second.tmmbr.erase(it);
1129 } else {
1130 candidates.push_back(it->second.tmmbr_item);
1131 ++it;
1132 }
1133 }
1134 }
1135 return candidates;
1136}
